# Step 3

Create a new model.

Create

```
lib/models/report_model.dart
```

Paste:

```dart
class ReportModel {

  final String patientName;

  final double hemoglobin;

  final double hba1c;

  final double vitaminD;

  ReportModel({

    required this.patientName,

    required this.hemoglobin,

    required this.hba1c,

    required this.vitaminD,

  });

  factory ReportModel.fromJson(Map<String, dynamic> json) {

    return ReportModel(

      patientName: json["patient_name"],

      hemoglobin: json["hemoglobin"].toDouble(),

      hba1c: json["hba1c"].toDouble(),

      vitaminD: json["vitamin_d"].toDouble(),

    );

  }

}
```

---

# Step 4

Replace your entire

```
lib/api/api_service.dart
```

with:

```dart
import 'dart:convert';

import 'package:http/http.dart' as http;

import '../models/report_model.dart';

class ApiService {

  Future<ReportModel> getReport() async {

    final response = await http.get(

      Uri.parse("http://192.168.29.33:8000/report"),

    );

    if (response.statusCode == 200) {

      return ReportModel.fromJson(

        jsonDecode(response.body),

      );

    }

    throw Exception("Failed to load report");

  }

}
```

> If your computer's IP address changes in the future, update the URL accordingly.

